
[1]tirade

   TIRA'DE, n.

   1. Formerly in French music, the filling of an interval by the
   intermediate diatonic notes.

   2. In modern usage, a strain or flight; a series of violent
   declamation.

   Here he delivers a violent tirade against all persons who profess to
   know any thing about angels.
